s://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"beside"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ج ن ب (j n b). Has the form of an active participle but the corresponding verb جَنَبَ (janaba, “to ward off”) has the wrong meaning."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒaː.nib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6432","headword_ar":"جَانِبٌ","root":"jnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAnibu","text_ar":"جَوَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobN","text_ar":"جَنْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in eleven places."},{"kind":"page_break","n":468},{"kind":"text","text":"[Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAna jaAnibuhu","text_ar":"لَانَ جَانِبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, gentle, easy to deal with, compliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obsequious."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN lay~inu AljaAnibi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ لَيِّنُ الجَانِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is gentle, easy to deal with, compliant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obsequious; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiyZu AljaAnibi","text_ar":"غَلِيظُ الجَانِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"glZ","text_ar":"غلظ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbN","text_ar":"جَنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuzan~u biliyni AljaAnibi","text_ar":"تُزَنُّ بِلِينِ الجَانِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She is suspected of easiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compliance"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lms","text_ar":"لمس"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards him who desires of her that he may lie with her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in that art.) [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibaA AlA^anofi","text_ar":"جَانِبَا الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbataA","text_ar":"جَنَابَتَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobataA","text_ar":"جَنْبَتَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janabataA","text_ar":"جَنَبَتَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides of the nose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two lines that surround the two sides of the nose"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a doe-gazelle: (Sb, TA:) pl. [of the second, agreeably with analogy,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAy^ibu","text_ar":"جَنَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbN","text_ar":"جَنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [It often signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vicinage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neighbourhood"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people &c.: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a region"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people or country: like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAHyp","text_ar":"ناحية"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bank"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a river; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any bank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steep acclivity."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A limit, bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boundary:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see a tropical usage of its pl. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAnibu","text_ar":"جَوَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") voce."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinowN","text_ar":"حِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY jaAnibK","text_ar":"عَلَى جَانِبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beside, aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibFA","text_ar":"جَانِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY jaAnibK","text_ar":"فِى جَانِبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN mino maAlK","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ مِنْ مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in posi-classical writings, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large portion, of property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, in the same,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large sum, of money."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b7-  The latter, also, in post-classical writings, signifies, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobN","text_ar":"جَنْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., (assumed tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation, which should be preserved inviolate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so used in the K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroDN","text_ar":"عِرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in an explanation of the latter word taken from IAth;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAmuwsN","text_ar":"نَامُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuromapN","text_ar":"حُرْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the TK in that case.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Avoided and despised."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, perhaps,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo ka*aA","text_ar":"دَعْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibFA","text_ar":"جَانِبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leave thou, such a thing alone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aw~N","text_ar":"اَوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubN","text_ar":"جُنُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b4-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujan~abN","text_ar":"مُجَنَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["CK","K","Sb","TA"]}]}}